                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15565875" author="shadow" created="Tue, 11 Oct 2016 16:16:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seeing that CXF devs started work on the 2.1 API, I noticed that there are still 2.0 parts missing &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Do you know of any plans to fix this?&lt;br/&gt;
Are there any other parts missing from 2.0?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15569058" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 12 Oct 2016 15:37:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve just added a test,&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/cxf/commit/9a46a89c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/cxf/commit/9a46a89c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looks like it was fixed for 3.1.7&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15569681" author="shadow" created="Wed, 12 Oct 2016 19:38:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seemed weird to still have missing functionalities for 2.0 after all this time &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
But I&apos;ve learned about &lt;tt&gt;ParamConverter&lt;/tt&gt; only recently, when trying to use a Joda DateTime as param and I didn&apos;t understand how this doesn&apos;t work in 2016 :-/&lt;br/&gt;
I actually thought the &lt;tt&gt;jackson-datatype-joda&lt;/tt&gt; module would take care of the conversion, but it seems I just misunderstood how these things work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe CXF should provide some &lt;tt&gt;ParamConverters&lt;/tt&gt; for usual types, like dates (both Joda and JSR 310)?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15571426" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2016 09:35:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What is weird about it ? We try the best to make it as complete as possible. To be honest, JAX-RS 2.0 Configurable is confusing, my initial understanding was that it was prepared for registering the providers which can be sorted (writers/readers, client request/response filters). Ex, there&apos;s a method which accepts an Integer priority, with the other methods defaulting to the default priority - which has no sense for ParamConverterProvider.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15571451" author="shadow" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2016 09:49:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, it seemed weird just because I was under the assumption that the support is complete &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Any thoughts about my suggestion with ParamConverters for some usual types?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15571462" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2016 09:54:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Converter is typically a few lines of code, having CXF shipping various converters for 3rd party libraries types would be problematic; it is better for the users to write their own code to maintain the converter portability&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
